14 MICHIGAN VETERANS' FACILITY AUTHORITY
15 Sec. 502. (1) From the funds appropriated in part 1, the MVH
16 and the MVFA shall provide compassionate and quality nursing care
17 services at each veterans' facility in this state so that resident
18 members can achieve their highest potential of wellness,
19 independence, self-worth, and dignity. The MVFA and the MVH shall
20 provide nursing care services to veterans in accordance with
21 federal standards and report the results of the annual USDVA and
22 CMS surveys and certification as proof of compliance.
23 (2) Appropriations in part 1 for a veterans' facility shall
24 not be used for any purpose other than expenses related to the
25 operations of the veterans' facility.
26 Sec. 503. All contractors providing health care services at a
27 veterans' facility shall provide services in a manner that complies
28 with applicable USDVA and CMS regulations for state veterans' homes
29 and skilled nursing facilities, any rules governing the operation
STM S06114'26 (S-1) 1emz5s

42
1 of nursing homes licensed in this state, and any training and
2 education requirements associated with staff licensure or
3 certification.
4 Sec. 504. (1) The MVFA shall report and investigate all
5 complaints of abuse or neglect at a veterans' facility in
6 compliance with USDVA and CMS regulations for state veterans' homes
7 and skilled nursing facilities. The MVFA shall report on a
8 bimonthly basis the following information:
9 (a) A description of the process by which resident members and
10 others may file complaints of alleged abuse or neglect at a
11 veterans' facility.
12 (b) Summary statistics on the number and general nature of
13 complaints of abuse or neglect.
14 (c) Summary statistics on the final disposition of complaints
15 of abuse or neglect received.
16 (2) The MVFA shall display in high-traffic areas throughout
17 the veterans' facility the process by which visitors, resident
18 members, and staff of the veterans' facility may register
19 complaints.
20 Sec. 505. The MVH shall do the following regarding member
21 care:
22 (a) Provide board-certified psychiatric care for all resident
23 members with mental health disorders in order to ensure that those
24 resident members receive needed services in a professional and
25 timely manner.
26 (b) Provide all resident members and staff a safe and secure
27 environment.
28 (c) Ensure that the veterans' facility effectively develops,
29 executes, and monitors all comprehensive care plans in accordance
STM S06114'26 (S-1) 1emz5s

43
1 with federal regulations and the veterans' facility's internal
2 policies, with a goal that a comprehensive care plan is fully
3 developed for all resident members.
4 Sec. 506. The MVH shall establish and implement internal
5 controls regarding all of the following:
6 (a) The use and management of food, maintenance, and
7 pharmaceutical and medical supply inventories.
8 (b) Calculating resident member maintenance assessments in
9 order to accurately calculate resident member maintenance
10 assessments for each billing cycle and ensure that all past due
11 resident member maintenance assessments are addressed within 30
12 days.
13 (c) Monetary donations and donated goods.
14 (d) The handling of resident member funds to ensure the
15 release of funds within 15 calendar days upon the resident member
16 leaving the home and to ensure that a representative of a resident
17 member is provided a full accounting of that resident member's
18 funds within 30 calendar days after the death of that resident
19 member.
20 (e) Financial reporting and accounting.
21 Sec. 507. (1) The MVH shall post on its website the following:
22 (a) All policies adopted by the MVFA and the veterans'
23 facility related to the administrative operations of the veterans'
24 facility.
25 (b) The agenda and minutes of public meetings of the MVFA
26 board.
27 (2) The MVH shall provide a report with copies of each
28 veterans' facility's USDVA State Veteran Home quarterly report.
29 These quarterly reports shall also be posted on the MVH website and
