8 DEPARTMENT OF MILITARY AND VETERANS AFFAIRS
9 Sec. 1301. (1) Funds appropriated in part 1A for Selfridge Air
10 National Guard Base must be used to support costs of runway
11 encroachment solutions while complying with air installation
12 compatible use zone program recommendations, including, but not
13 limited to, all of the following:
14 (a) Capital improvements necessary to shift the runway to the
15 north and repair the airfield and nonairfield features of the base
16 and surrounding community impacted by the shift.
17 (b) Infrastructure projects including, but not limited to,
18 roadways repairs, vehicle access to the base and to the museum,
19 stormwater drain and culvert repairs and modernization, force
20 protection features, airfield features, and taxiway extensions.
21 (2) Unexpended funds appropriated in part 1A for Selfridge Air
22 National Guard Base are designated as a work project appropriation.
23 Unencumbered or unallotted funds shall not lapse at the end of the
24 fiscal year and shall be available for expenditures under this
25 section until the project has been completed. The following is in
26 compliance with section 451a of the management and budget act, 1984
27 PA 431, MCL 18.1451a:
28 (a) The purpose of the project is to support costs of runway
29 encroachment solutions.
